abstract_one = """Accurate and comprehensive identification of cancer-associated genetic changes is the goal of precision medicine. Current clinical testing methods are incomplete as they fail to capture the full spectrum of disease-causing genetic variation in any one individual or tumor. Long-read sequencing (LRS) is an emerging technology that generates sequencing reads tens to hundreds of thousands of base pairs in length along with epigenetic information. These longer reads can capture variation in challenging regions and identify complex genetic changes, such as large structural variants, provide phasing information to identify biallelic mutational status, and can directly identify methylation or base pair modifications. We have generated pilot data showing that as a single test LRS can identify disease-causing variation in individuals with acute myeloid leukemia (AML) that is currently identified using multiple genetic approaches (e.g., short read sequencing, karyotype, and array). This application aims to build a new interdisciplinary partnership to develop an LRS-based methylation classifier to be used to rapidly evaluate individuals with AML, allowing methylation to act 1) as a separate validation of the sequencing-based findings, and 2) be used to rapidly identify a tumor type. Development of methylation-based classification for AML will support applications for additional funding to apply these methods to other tumor types and be used in the development of LRS-based clinical testing for AML."""
a1 = ("Abstract 1", abstract_one)
